  "body": "# Rationale\r\n\r\nRight now, Caplin spends a big amount of its memory copying large memory for beacon states. A way to alleviate it is to use a pre-allocated beacon state for every operation instead of creating a new copy.\r\n\r\n# Implementation\r\n\r\nAdd `CopyInto` to Beacon State which is going to take another beacon state as the external buffer and copy the state into it. NOTE: this includes also caches. those re tricky :)",
